RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pandect
<hw>Pan"dect</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pandecta</ets>, <ets>pandectes</ets>, Gr. <?/ all-receiving,
all-containing; <grk>pa^s</grk>, <grk>pa^n</grk>, all + <?/ to receive:
cf. F. <ets>pandectes</ets>, pl.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A treatise
which comprehends the whole of any science.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Thou] a <qex>pandect</qex> mak'st, and universal book.</q>
<rj><qau>Donne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>The digest, or abridgment, in fifty
books, of the decisions, writings, and opinions of the old Roman
jurists, made in the sixth century by direction of the emperor
Justinian, and forming the leading compilation of the Roman civil
law.</def> <rj><au>Kent.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pandemic</ent>⟦br⟧
